[accomplishment]
title=Fixing a bug by yourself
description=Fixed a bug in which you are the assignee
collection=ubuntu-community
category=QA
icon=devel.png
depends=ubuntu-community/report-first-bug
needs-signing=true
needs-information=launchpad-email
summary = A bug is a defect in a piece of software. Ubuntu needs a lot of volunteers to help and fixing bugs is one of the things that a developer can do. We do hope that people can help us to fix the bugs. Please be reminded that only bugs of "Ubuntu" will be counted.
steps= 1. Find a bug
2. Mark yourself as assignee
3. Branch your code using bzr
4. Fix the bug
5. Upload your code to Launchpad
6. Request a merge
7. If it was merged the bug will be marked as "Fix released". Then you will get this accomplishment!
links: http://www.ubuntu.com
       http://developer.ubuntu.com/packaging/html/fixing-a-bug.html
help =  #ubuntu-motu on Freenode
author = Howard Chan <smartboyhw@gmail.com>
